WEBVTT

1
00:00:22.564 --> 00:00:24.733
We're averaging about 300 barrels a day.

2
00:00:25.275 --> 00:00:27.110
That's a pretty steep increase.

3
00:00:29.947 --> 00:00:32.533
Don't worry. He's got it.

4
00:00:34.159 --> 00:00:36.119
You're sure givin' him a long leash.

5
00:00:37.496 --> 00:00:38.789
I know what I'm doing.

6
00:00:40.040 --> 00:00:41.542
My regulation license.

7
00:00:42.167 --> 00:00:43.585
How are the kids?

8
00:00:43.669 --> 00:00:45.462
Well. oldest is off to college.

9
00:00:46.380 --> 00:00:47.381
That'll cost you.

10
00:00:48.298 --> 00:00:49.716
You're telling me.

11
00:00:49.800 --> 00:00:50.843
This will help.

12
00:01:00.394 --> 00:01:01.520
Sign here.

13
00:01:20.205 --> 00:01:21.415
Was I making you nervous?

14
00:01:22.124 --> 00:01:23.125
How did that go?

15
00:01:23.625 --> 00:01:25.794
We've got State sign-off
for the next 12 months.

16
00:01:28.463 --> 00:01:30.757
I'm gonna need you
to slow down our output.

17
00:01:30.841 --> 00:01:33.510
We're generating more cash
than I can safely move.

18
00:01:34.636 --> 00:01:36.221
You're welcome.

19
00:01:36.305 --> 00:01:37.723
Don't get cocky.

20
00:01:37.806 --> 00:01:39.474
Confidence is currency.

21
00:01:39.558 --> 00:01:41.852
No. John. Currency is currency.

22
00:02:02.831 --> 00:02:03.957
What?

23
00:02:05.042 --> 00:02:06.752
You could have told me
we were coming here.

24
00:02:07.336 --> 00:02:08.669
It's just a quick stop.

25
00:02:09.755 --> 00:02:11.757
You know I don't want
anything to do with this.

26
00:02:12.424 --> 00:02:13.759
Which part?

27
00:02:13.842 --> 00:02:15.969
This. Her. All of it.

28
00:02:16.720 --> 00:02:17.846
Come on. Trust me.

29
00:02:18.514 --> 00:02:20.015
We got a good thing going here.

30
00:02:28.106 --> 00:02:29.691
This is not going to end well.

31
00:04:40.781 --> 00:04:42.241
How long has he been like that?

32
00:04:42.324 --> 00:04:43.534
Couple hours.

33
00:04:44.910 --> 00:04:46.078
What'd you get?

34
00:04:46.161 --> 00:04:47.621
Nothing. He's not talking.

35
00:04:49.122 --> 00:04:50.541
This was in his wallet.

36
00:04:55.546 --> 00:04:57.881
All right. Get the toolbox out of the truck.

37
00:05:30.539 --> 00:05:32.457
They did a real number on you?

38
00:05:32.958 --> 00:05:34.543
No. look at me. Mr. Miller?

39
00:05:35.794 --> 00:05:37.754
Look at me. Mr. Miller.

40
00:05:40.132 --> 00:05:41.633
My name's Dutch.

41
00:05:41.717 --> 00:05:45.012
And I… I work for the woman
who put that bullet in your foot.

42
00:05:48.182 --> 00:05:49.183
Here. You want one?

43
00:05:49.266 --> 00:05:50.434
What?

44
00:05:50.517 --> 00:05:51.643
You want one?

45
00:05:52.728 --> 00:05:55.189
- No.
- I'm trying to quit smoking.

46
00:05:55.272 --> 00:05:56.273
It's…

47
00:05:57.566 --> 00:05:58.942
So. the woman I work for.

48
00:05:59.026 --> 00:06:02.070
she is a mother
who is trying to find her son.

49
00:06:02.946 --> 00:06:05.449
Something chemical happens.
something animalistic.

50
00:06:05.532 --> 00:06:08.202
when a mother is separated from her young.

51
00:06:08.285 --> 00:06:10.162
I'd help you. if I could.

52
00:06:10.245 --> 00:06:12.289
I swear. I don't know the guy.

53
00:06:20.881 --> 00:06:24.051
See. the thing about
a broken nose isn't so much the pain…

54
00:06:25.219 --> 00:06:26.970
…although it hurts like hell.

55
00:06:27.638 --> 00:06:30.998
But it also changes your breathing because
you're only breathing from your mouth now.

56
00:06:31.391 --> 00:06:33.769
So. let's see if we could.
you know. speed things up here.

57
00:06:34.353 --> 00:06:35.604
What?

58
00:06:35.687 --> 00:06:39.650
God. No. no. no. no. no.
My God. No. please.

59
00:06:40.484 --> 00:06:41.860
Please. I…

60
00:06:47.115 --> 00:06:49.493
- No. Please don't...
- Cary Masterson.

61
00:06:49.576 --> 00:06:51.745
I don't… I d… I don't know him.

62
00:06:51.828 --> 00:06:53.539
I don't know him. I don't know.

63
00:06:53.622 --> 00:06:55.290
We know Cary came to see you.

64
00:06:55.374 --> 00:06:56.375
No.

65
00:06:56.458 --> 00:06:57.626
We know what you do.

66
00:06:58.627 --> 00:07:00.546
Did you make a new ID for Cary Masterson?

67
00:07:00.629 --> 00:07:02.381
I don't make IDs. man.

68
00:07:02.464 --> 00:07:07.219
I don't know. I just fucking…
No. this is all a big mistake.

69
00:07:07.302 --> 00:07:09.388
My God. God. Nope.

70
00:07:09.471 --> 00:07:10.889
Please. Please.

71
00:07:10.973 --> 00:07:12.224
Please. No.

72
00:07:20.190 --> 00:07:21.400
Hey.

73
00:07:21.483 --> 00:07:22.776
Morning.

74
00:07:23.861 --> 00:07:24.987
How was your ride?

75
00:07:25.070 --> 00:07:27.239
It was lovely. Really cleared my head.

76
00:07:31.451 --> 00:07:33.287
So. no luck?

77
00:07:34.204 --> 00:07:37.249
- Please. I beg you. I don't know.
- Yeah. he doesn't know anything.

78
00:07:39.626 --> 00:07:40.627
That's a bummer.

79
00:07:41.253 --> 00:07:43.422
- Just finish him quietly.
- W-What?

80
00:07:43.505 --> 00:07:45.716
- I don't want to spook the horses.
- D-Don't go.

81
00:07:45.799 --> 00:07:47.551
- Of course.
- God. No. come back.

82
00:07:49.678 --> 00:07:50.971
What about me?

83
00:07:51.054 --> 00:07:52.055
No.

84
00:07:53.932 --> 00:07:55.934
I don't. I… Please. I beg you.

85
00:07:56.018 --> 00:07:57.352
I don't know. I don't know him.

86
00:07:57.436 --> 00:07:58.770
I don't… I don't know...

87
00:08:33.597 --> 00:08:37.226
You have a collect call
from an inmate at LOMPOC Federal Prison.

88
00:08:37.308 --> 00:08:38.936
John Armstrong.

89
00:08:39.019 --> 00:08:40.270
Press one to accept.

90
00:08:41.980 --> 00:08:44.691
- Dad.
- Been trying you.

91
00:08:44.775 --> 00:08:47.110
- I need you to tell me what to do.
- You okay?

92
00:08:48.612 --> 00:08:51.114
- I'm not gonna make it.
- Of course you're going to make it.

93
00:08:52.157 --> 00:08:54.910
You don't… You don't get it.
People are dying. Dad.

94
00:08:58.664 --> 00:08:59.790
No. not on the phone.

95
00:09:01.500 --> 00:09:04.044
Figure out your next move.
Get somewhere safe.

96
00:09:04.127 --> 00:09:07.130
Next time I call you.
be in a better place. Say it back to me.

97
00:09:07.214 --> 00:09:09.550
- I'm gonna be in a better place.
- Say it back to me.

98
00:09:09.633 --> 00:09:11.051
I'm gonna be in a better place.

99
00:09:13.011 --> 00:09:14.137
Lucky?

100
00:10:32.674 --> 00:10:35.552
How come everything
this girl touches goes up in flames?

101
00:10:36.053 --> 00:10:37.763
She could be anywhere right now.

102
00:10:39.097 --> 00:10:40.950
Look. I know this isn't what you want
to hear...

103
00:10:40.974 --> 00:10:42.226
Then don't tell me.

104
00:10:42.726 --> 00:10:46.104
So. we dug up a reservation
at this car rental company in Vegas.

105
00:10:46.188 --> 00:10:49.399
- We already found the car.
- No. this is a different one.

106
00:10:50.484 --> 00:10:52.027
It's booked under Priscilla's name

107
00:10:52.110 --> 00:10:54.071
and it's the same day
they arrived in Vegas.

108
00:10:54.613 --> 00:10:56.698
I think that's the car that Cary left in.

109
00:10:57.824 --> 00:10:58.951
So. maybe we should pivot.

110
00:11:00.452 --> 00:11:01.954
- Pivot?
- Yes.

111
00:11:02.829 --> 00:11:04.331
Now is not the time to pivot.

112
00:11:05.123 --> 00:11:06.917
She was just here. We're close.

113
00:11:08.836 --> 00:11:13.173
We're no closer than we were in Vegas.
You're already on thin ice with Kershaw.

114
00:11:13.257 --> 00:11:14.883
You let me worry about Kershaw.

115
00:11:14.967 --> 00:11:16.593
I would if you did.

116
00:11:16.677 --> 00:11:19.596
You just keep ignoring procedure. Rand.

117
00:11:19.680 --> 00:11:21.241
I know you think
that's what makes you good.

118
00:11:21.265 --> 00:11:23.475
but this is twice now
she's gotten away from you.

119
00:11:24.142 --> 00:11:26.103
We need to be operating
on facts. not feelings.

120
00:11:26.186 --> 00:11:27.938
Sometimes a feeling is all you got.

121
00:11:28.689 --> 00:11:30.899
I'm just gonna pretend
like you didn't just say that.

122
00:11:34.736 --> 00:11:35.988
Gates!

123
00:11:37.197 --> 00:11:39.575
- You want to pursue the car rental?
- Yes.

124
00:11:39.658 --> 00:11:41.326
Pursue the car rental.

125
00:11:41.410 --> 00:11:43.370
But you watch who you're talking to.

126
00:11:43.453 --> 00:11:46.206
- I'm just looking out for you. ma'am.
- You're looking out for you.

127
00:12:11.398 --> 00:12:13.108
It's probably a mistake.

128
00:12:13.192 --> 00:12:14.318
Which part?

129
00:12:15.819 --> 00:12:18.780
Asking him to choose
between his mother and his wife.

130
00:12:20.657 --> 00:12:21.909
Had he chosen her.

131
00:12:21.992 --> 00:12:23.827
she wouldn't have been out in the desert…

132
00:12:24.328 --> 00:12:25.495
Alone like that.

133
00:12:28.457 --> 00:12:29.666
You could be right.

134
00:12:30.584 --> 00:12:33.879
I thought for sure that she'd turned him.
but now I…

135
00:12:33.962 --> 00:12:35.380
I saw it on her face.

136
00:12:36.215 --> 00:12:38.842
She doesn't know where he is any…
any more than we do.

137
00:12:39.510 --> 00:12:42.346
So. what happened?
What could possibly have happened?

138
00:12:43.805 --> 00:12:47.935
Well. maybe he flashed some cash
to the wrong people. Got rolled?

139
00:12:49.811 --> 00:12:51.396
And what? They killed him?

140
00:12:55.234 --> 00:12:56.652
Why was his car in Long Beach?

141
00:12:57.444 --> 00:12:58.987
Throw us off. maybe.

142
00:13:18.173 --> 00:13:19.174
I don't know.

143
00:13:19.967 --> 00:13:21.093
I…

144
00:13:21.844 --> 00:13:26.098
I'm gonna take a long shower
and I'm gonna think about what to do next.

145
00:13:27.140 --> 00:13:30.018
And you're gonna take care
of that poor schmuck in the stables.

146
00:13:31.311 --> 00:13:32.896
There's no one in the stables.

147
00:13:32.980 --> 00:13:34.940
Schmucks or otherwise.

148
00:13:35.023 --> 00:13:36.316
I got sloppy.

149
00:13:38.485 --> 00:13:39.570
Your son is missing.

150
00:13:41.864 --> 00:13:44.157
Anything goes. until he ain't.

151
00:13:47.286 --> 00:13:48.912
And Lucky?

152
00:13:49.580 --> 00:13:50.831
What's her angle?

153
00:13:52.249 --> 00:13:53.750
We'll ask her when we find her.

154
00:14:23.530 --> 00:14:25.282
Here you go. Enjoy.

155
00:14:25.365 --> 00:14:29.286
You ready? Yeah. you're ready. Okay.

156
00:14:31.163 --> 00:14:32.247
My God.

157
00:14:39.922 --> 00:14:42.674
- Hey. can I help you?
- My God. Thank you.

158
00:14:42.758 --> 00:14:44.218
- I got you.
- Thank you.

159
00:14:44.301 --> 00:14:46.178
The things women hold.

160
00:14:47.387 --> 00:14:48.931
Have I seen you at school before?

161
00:14:49.014 --> 00:14:50.849
No. I don't think so.

162
00:14:50.933 --> 00:14:52.613
Naomi just hired me to help with the kids.

163
00:14:52.643 --> 00:14:54.394
- Let me grab that for you.
- Thank you.

164
00:14:54.478 --> 00:14:55.687
- Yep.
- Hey. little man.

165
00:14:56.480 --> 00:14:57.481
Wanna take my hand?

166
00:14:57.564 --> 00:14:59.983
- Sure.
- Okay. let's go.

167
00:15:00.567 --> 00:15:03.487
Happy birthday to Marcus.

168
00:15:04.112 --> 00:15:05.155
- Yep.
- Yep.

169
00:15:05.239 --> 00:15:07.032
- Are you excited?
- Yep.

170
00:15:07.115 --> 00:15:10.077
Do you think there'll be
some birthday cake?

171
00:15:10.577 --> 00:15:11.662
Cake.

172
00:15:11.745 --> 00:15:14.122
Cake is good.

173
00:15:14.206 --> 00:15:15.958
Especially the frosting.

174
00:15:16.041 --> 00:15:19.086
- The frosting is delicious. isn't it?
- Yeah.

175
00:15:28.178 --> 00:15:34.142
Okay. honey. Why don't you go play
with your mama?

176
00:15:34.893 --> 00:15:37.604
Don't worry about this.
You guys enjoy the party.

177
00:15:37.688 --> 00:15:38.772
There we go.

178
00:15:42.693 --> 00:15:44.194
All right. Lucky. Where are you?

179
00:16:04.506 --> 00:16:05.757
Come on.

180
00:16:13.849 --> 00:16:14.850
There we go.

181
00:16:23.150 --> 00:16:24.860
Where are you? Where are you?

182
00:16:42.753 --> 00:16:44.671
There you are.

183
00:17:14.034 --> 00:17:15.035
Okay.

184
00:17:25.378 --> 00:17:26.755
My God.

185
00:17:26.839 --> 00:17:28.507
Nice dress.

186
00:17:30.175 --> 00:17:33.554
Don't worry about it. We've all done it.
It's a ridiculous spread.

187
00:17:34.388 --> 00:17:35.681
Right?

188
00:17:35.764 --> 00:17:37.884
I mean. she told me to come up here
because. you know…

189
00:17:37.933 --> 00:17:41.395
I spilled a little wine. you know? But I
did not expect that it was going to be…

190
00:17:41.478 --> 00:17:43.272
Fucking Bergdorf Goodman?

191
00:17:43.355 --> 00:17:44.356
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

192
00:17:44.439 --> 00:17:46.292
Take a Birkin while you're at it.
She won't notice.

193
00:17:46.316 --> 00:17:48.861
Plus. Neil's gonna get everything
in the divorce anyway.

194
00:17:49.653 --> 00:17:50.737
I heard.

195
00:17:51.321 --> 00:17:52.322
Poor Naomi.

196
00:17:52.823 --> 00:17:53.866
It's for the best.

197
00:17:54.449 --> 00:17:57.160
Neil is human sandpaper.

198
00:17:58.370 --> 00:17:59.580
Yeah. It's…

199
00:18:01.039 --> 00:18:03.041
Something in the way he chews. right?

200
00:18:03.125 --> 00:18:05.377
- It's very pronounced.
- My God.

201
00:18:05.460 --> 00:18:09.464
I have had to fake a migraine
just to get out of dinner with them.

202
00:18:09.548 --> 00:18:10.716
I understand that.

203
00:18:12.009 --> 00:18:14.803
- You look gorgeous in that dress.
- Thanks. I mean…

204
00:18:14.887 --> 00:18:17.181
Yeah. a… Actually.
could you help me with it?

205
00:18:17.264 --> 00:18:19.808
I'm not really sure how
my dress is supposed to go.

206
00:18:19.892 --> 00:18:21.226
- Like is it…
- Yeah.

207
00:18:21.935 --> 00:18:22.936
That's right.

208
00:18:23.478 --> 00:18:24.688
Your dress.

209
00:18:27.274 --> 00:18:28.483
What's your name?

210
00:18:28.567 --> 00:18:30.819
- Sharon.
- Hey. Sharon. I'm Amy.

211
00:18:31.570 --> 00:18:33.989
- There we go. One more.
- Let me see.

212
00:18:35.407 --> 00:18:36.783
- Yeah.
- Sharon.

213
00:18:36.867 --> 00:18:37.868
See?

214
00:18:37.951 --> 00:18:38.994
This way.

215
00:18:39.077 --> 00:18:40.829
- Where's my purse?
- You got it?

216
00:18:40.913 --> 00:18:43.393
- Yeah. Yeah. yeah. yeah.
- Okay. Okay. Okay. okay. okay. okay.

217
00:18:45.167 --> 00:18:46.877
Let's do a shot. Yes!

218
00:18:46.960 --> 00:18:48.480
- That's a great idea.
- It's ridiculous

219
00:18:48.504 --> 00:18:50.624
I even drive to these things.
I always end up Ubering.

220
00:18:52.925 --> 00:18:54.194
- I love your dress.
- Excuse me.

221
00:18:54.218 --> 00:18:57.012
- Thank you so much. I appreciate you.
- Come on. Come on.

222
00:18:58.180 --> 00:18:59.431
Don Julio for the ladies.

223
00:19:00.891 --> 00:19:02.226
Sharon. you are so fun.

224
00:19:02.309 --> 00:19:05.395
- Thank you. You're fun.
- Thank you for this. I needed it.

225
00:19:06.813 --> 00:19:08.065
- To you.
- To you.

226
00:19:12.361 --> 00:19:13.403
Yeah.

227
00:19:38.804 --> 00:19:40.347
You see those gifts over there?

228
00:19:40.848 --> 00:19:43.308
You're gonna grab any cards
that aren't attached to presents.

229
00:19:43.392 --> 00:19:44.935
Those are the ones with cash.

230
00:19:45.018 --> 00:19:46.937
Then. hit the purses.

231
00:19:47.020 --> 00:19:48.105
They're gonna see me.

232
00:19:48.188 --> 00:19:50.649
No. they're not.
You're going to be invisible.

233
00:19:51.358 --> 00:19:52.598
How am I going to be invisible?

234
00:19:52.651 --> 00:19:54.778
I'm not even invited to this party.

235
00:19:54.862 --> 00:19:56.780
Invisibility is a matter of environment.

236
00:19:56.864 --> 00:19:59.741
- Watch very closely.
- And at a kid's birthday party…

237
00:19:59.825 --> 00:20:01.118
Very slowly…

238
00:20:01.201 --> 00:20:03.745
…the most invisible thing is a kid.

239
00:20:05.038 --> 00:20:06.290
Okay.

240
00:20:10.377 --> 00:20:11.378
Not yet.

241
00:20:12.379 --> 00:20:13.297
Now.

242
00:20:13.380 --> 00:20:14.631
Now.

243
00:20:30.314 --> 00:20:33.025
Welcome to the fun
Where the free market won.

244
00:20:33.108 --> 00:20:34.276
And money is a crown.

245
00:20:34.359 --> 00:20:37.529
And nothing trickles down
That isn't bleeding.

246
00:20:41.992 --> 00:20:44.578
Hungry little ants
With their hands down their pants.

247
00:20:44.661 --> 00:20:45.954
Wanna take care of themselves.

248
00:20:46.038 --> 00:20:49.416
Before everybody else. a little greedy.

249
00:20:50.542 --> 00:20:53.295
They get so good at thievin'
That they never stop believin'

250
00:20:53.378 --> 00:20:56.715
That it's mine. mine. mine. mine
Mine. mine. mine.

251
00:20:58.926 --> 00:21:01.845
Mine. mine. mine. mine
Mine. mine. mine.

252
00:21:04.056 --> 00:21:06.683
Mine. mine. mine. mine. mine. mine.

253
00:21:09.686 --> 00:21:12.731
Mine. mine. mine. mine
Mine. mine. mine.

254
00:21:14.983 --> 00:21:17.945
Mine. mine. mine. mine
Mine. mine. mine.

255
00:21:20.072 --> 00:21:22.616
Mine. mine. mine. mine. mine. mine.

256
00:21:24.034 --> 00:21:26.662
Starting route to 418 Baxter Street.

257
00:21:26.745 --> 00:21:29.164
Go straight on Pacific Coast Highway
for ten miles.

258
00:22:27.347 --> 00:22:29.433
Did you find what you were looking for?

259
00:22:35.189 --> 00:22:38.358
You always use bleach
when you clean your stables?

260
00:22:38.442 --> 00:22:41.445
I wouldn't know.
I leave that to the ranch hands.

261
00:22:42.613 --> 00:22:43.614
Yeah.

262
00:22:44.239 --> 00:22:46.200
I know you don't like
to get your hands dirty.

263
00:22:46.283 --> 00:22:49.203
I think if you were here to tell me
that my son is dead.

264
00:22:49.286 --> 00:22:50.996
you would knock on the front door.

265
00:22:52.831 --> 00:22:53.999
I don't know where Cary is.

266
00:22:54.082 --> 00:22:55.083
But I do know…

267
00:22:56.126 --> 00:22:57.836
I do know that he's in a lot of trouble.

268
00:22:57.920 --> 00:22:59.963
Tell me. Agent Rand. Do you have kids?

269
00:23:03.717 --> 00:23:04.801
Of course you won't answer.

270
00:23:04.885 --> 00:23:08.138
because you're afraid I'd come after them
the way you're coming after mine.

271
00:23:08.639 --> 00:23:10.265
Your son is a grown man.

272
00:23:11.433 --> 00:23:13.060
A grown-ass man.

273
00:23:13.936 --> 00:23:15.270
who made his own decision.

274
00:23:15.354 --> 00:23:17.523
Yeah. why are you here. Agent Rand?

275
00:23:17.606 --> 00:23:19.483
Just following up on a lead.

276
00:23:21.109 --> 00:23:22.653
Yeah. that's bullshit.

277
00:23:22.736 --> 00:23:25.656
This isn't about Cary.
This is about you and me.

278
00:23:26.156 --> 00:23:29.201
I was a career-making bust for you
and it didn't stick.

279
00:23:29.952 --> 00:23:31.286
It'll stick this time.

280
00:23:32.412 --> 00:23:34.039
Yeah. You see. that was…

281
00:23:35.082 --> 00:23:36.959
That was a federal agent…

282
00:23:37.876 --> 00:23:39.336
Your people ran over.

283
00:23:41.004 --> 00:23:42.089
One of my agents.

284
00:23:42.172 --> 00:23:44.091
I'm sure I don't know
what you're talking about.

285
00:23:45.259 --> 00:23:48.804
But we both know that if you had anything
on me. you'd be arresting me.

286
00:23:49.763 --> 00:23:52.243
All in due time. I could arrest Dutch
right now if I wanted to.

287
00:23:52.307 --> 00:23:54.059
Unfortunately he's not here.

288
00:23:54.142 --> 00:23:58.021
Really? Because he was driving
that truck right there last night.

289
00:24:01.650 --> 00:24:03.151
Did he commit a crime?

290
00:24:03.902 --> 00:24:04.903
Many.

291
00:24:05.571 --> 00:24:06.947
But I'm going to leave him alone.

292
00:24:08.615 --> 00:24:11.326
I'm gonna let him help you

293
00:24:12.244 --> 00:24:14.037
dig your hole a little deeper.

294
00:24:14.997 --> 00:24:17.416
You want it too badly. Agent Rand.

295
00:24:24.840 --> 00:24:25.841
Maybe.

296
00:24:33.223 --> 00:24:34.224
We know…

297
00:24:36.310 --> 00:24:39.354
That you rented that car for Cary.

298
00:24:39.980 --> 00:24:41.690
And we're gonna find him.

299
00:24:41.773 --> 00:24:46.153
And you better hope we find him
before Whittaker does.

300
00:24:48.697 --> 00:24:49.907
That car's a dead end.

301
00:24:51.992 --> 00:24:52.993
Really?

302
00:24:55.579 --> 00:24:56.663
What about Lucky?

303
00:24:58.040 --> 00:24:59.041
What about her?

304
00:25:04.922 --> 00:25:06.048
You really don't know.

305
00:25:10.802 --> 00:25:14.139
After Dutch shot up
the service station last night.

306
00:25:14.223 --> 00:25:17.726
Lucky hitched a ride
in the bed of his truck.

307
00:25:18.769 --> 00:25:20.771
That truck right there.

308
00:25:20.854 --> 00:25:24.066
The one you say you know nothing about.

309
00:25:28.529 --> 00:25:30.531
She was right under your nose…

310
00:25:32.282 --> 00:25:33.575
The whole time.

311
00:25:37.079 --> 00:25:38.080
Priscilla.

312
00:25:43.043 --> 00:25:44.253
I'll see myself out.

313
00:26:05.190 --> 00:26:08.735
GPS from Cary Masterson's
rental car is coming your way.

314
00:26:08.819 --> 00:26:09.820
It's a dead end.

315
00:26:09.903 --> 00:26:13.198
Just because following his car is my plan
doesn't mean you should dismiss it.

316
00:26:13.699 --> 00:26:16.785
Gates. the car lead
is not going anywhere. He ditched it.

317
00:26:16.869 --> 00:26:17.953
How do you know?

318
00:26:18.036 --> 00:26:19.037
It doesn't matter.

319
00:26:19.121 --> 00:26:20.706
So where does that leave us?

320
00:26:20.789 --> 00:26:24.459
I want you to check every car dealership
in southern California.

321
00:26:24.543 --> 00:26:28.547
I want a list of everybody who paid cash
for a car in the last two days.

322
00:26:29.256 --> 00:26:31.091
What makes you think he bought a new car?

323
00:26:31.717 --> 00:26:35.179
He's a 29-year-old man with
$10 million burning a hole in his pocket.

324
00:26:35.888 --> 00:26:37.222
Call it a feeling.

325
00:27:01.079 --> 00:27:02.331
Hello?

326
00:28:02.641 --> 00:28:03.642
You lost?

327
00:28:05.435 --> 00:28:07.938
Yeah. Maybe. A little.

328
00:28:11.149 --> 00:28:15.195
You know what. don't worry about it.
This was a complete waste of time.

329
00:28:15.279 --> 00:28:16.280
This was a mistake.

330
00:28:16.363 --> 00:28:17.447
Why are you here?

331
00:28:20.325 --> 00:28:24.621
'Cause I was told maybe you could help me.

332
00:28:25.497 --> 00:28:26.832
Or somebody here could.

333
00:28:27.958 --> 00:28:30.419
Maybe. Depends on what you need.

334
00:28:33.964 --> 00:28:34.965
I…

335
00:28:36.967 --> 00:28:39.970
Need to become someone else.

336
00:28:43.265 --> 00:28:44.558
How'd you find me?

337
00:28:46.226 --> 00:28:47.728
Honestly. some guy on Reddit.

338
00:28:49.354 --> 00:28:50.898
- Reddit?
- Yeah. I know.

339
00:28:50.981 --> 00:28:52.691
I just didn't know where to look.

340
00:28:54.776 --> 00:28:56.778
I have never done this before.

341
00:28:57.362 --> 00:28:58.822
Yeah. Most people haven't.

342
00:28:58.906 --> 00:28:59.907
Right.

343
00:29:03.410 --> 00:29:04.953
Why do you want to disappear?

344
00:29:05.037 --> 00:29:06.205
Does it really matter?

345
00:29:07.247 --> 00:29:09.291
It will help me to know what you need.

346
00:29:10.751 --> 00:29:14.046
Right. Well. I need a divorce.

347
00:29:16.215 --> 00:29:17.925
- I'm not a lawyer.
- Yes.

348
00:29:18.008 --> 00:29:20.427
But I'm looking for something permanent.

349
00:29:22.262 --> 00:29:24.264
Don't want his name. don't want my name.

350
00:29:25.057 --> 00:29:28.268
Nothing that ties me to what I've become.

351
00:29:30.145 --> 00:29:31.897
Or what he's turned me into.

352
00:29:35.943 --> 00:29:37.183
Sorry. I wasn't ready for that.

353
00:29:37.653 --> 00:29:39.655
Sorry. You ready?

354
00:29:43.742 --> 00:29:45.327
What kind of people come to you?

355
00:29:46.245 --> 00:29:47.454
Is there really a kind?

356
00:29:47.538 --> 00:29:49.581
Some need health insurance.

357
00:29:49.665 --> 00:29:52.501
Some want to hide money
in banks with another name.

358
00:29:54.127 --> 00:29:56.421
Most just want to get into a bar.

359
00:29:56.505 --> 00:29:57.881
So not everyone's running?

360
00:29:58.382 --> 00:29:59.800
No.

361
00:30:00.592 --> 00:30:03.554
I think. deep down.
we all want freedom from ourselves.

362
00:30:03.637 --> 00:30:06.473
Have you ever heard
of punctuated equilibrium?

363
00:30:07.307 --> 00:30:08.475
No.

364
00:30:08.559 --> 00:30:10.060
It's an evolutionary theory.

365
00:30:10.143 --> 00:30:13.272
Extreme circumstances
require radical change.

366
00:30:14.398 --> 00:30:16.275
If you want to survive. at least.

367
00:30:21.780 --> 00:30:25.117
Here. These are misprints.
I use them as examples of what I can do.

368
00:30:25.200 --> 00:30:26.243
See what you like.

369
00:30:26.326 --> 00:30:27.327
Thank you.

370
00:30:27.911 --> 00:30:30.330
I'm gonna need a legit address
from you for the ID

371
00:30:30.414 --> 00:30:32.082
so I can link credit cards to it.

372
00:30:32.165 --> 00:30:33.166
Right.

373
00:30:55.564 --> 00:30:57.232
So do you know where you're going?

374
00:31:01.069 --> 00:31:02.196
Yeah.

375
00:31:12.456 --> 00:31:14.124
- Hello?
- Hey. kid.

376
00:31:15.250 --> 00:31:16.793
- Dad?
- I got a burner phone.

377
00:31:16.877 --> 00:31:18.295
Now we can talk freely.

378
00:31:21.089 --> 00:31:25.260
Well. I found him.
He changed his name. got a new ID.

379
00:31:27.304 --> 00:31:30.557
But I have his address.
and I am gonna get it back.

380
00:31:31.225 --> 00:31:33.977
Everything he stole from us. Dad.
I'm getting it back.

381
00:31:35.521 --> 00:31:38.899
Okay. Okay. good. Now. take a breath.

382
00:31:40.734 --> 00:31:42.444
- What do you mean? I'm fine.
- Honey.

383
00:31:42.528 --> 00:31:45.489
you just got confirmation
the man you love screwed you over.

384
00:31:45.572 --> 00:31:47.452
You don't think
you might be a little emotional?

385
00:31:47.533 --> 00:31:50.077
Can you just try
and not coach me right now?

386
00:31:50.744 --> 00:31:52.412
I… I swear I have it.

387
00:31:53.080 --> 00:31:54.790
This is about the money now.

388
00:31:54.873 --> 00:31:58.168
You pick your moment.
and then. like Zorro. you get in.

389
00:31:58.252 --> 00:32:00.546
you make your little "Z".
and you get the fuck out.

390
00:32:00.629 --> 00:32:02.881
Do not get it in your head

391
00:32:02.965 --> 00:32:06.301
to have some kind of reckoning
with him over this. Do you understand?

392
00:32:06.385 --> 00:32:08.220
Nothing he says will be good enough.

393
00:32:11.014 --> 00:32:12.367
And if he's willing to do this to you.

394
00:32:12.391 --> 00:32:14.643
we don't know what else
he's willing to do. right?

395
00:32:16.812 --> 00:32:17.813
Lucky?

396
00:32:20.774 --> 00:32:23.235
Yes. Yes. I got it. In and out.

397
00:32:59.980 --> 00:33:01.815
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

398
00:33:30.010 --> 00:33:32.596
- What are you staring at? Come on. What?
- No.

399
00:33:33.263 --> 00:33:37.100
No… You remind me of someone.

400
00:33:37.726 --> 00:33:39.144
- And…
- That's all.

401
00:33:39.228 --> 00:33:40.729
Is that a good thing?

402
00:33:40.812 --> 00:33:44.358
It was. Up until a few days ago.

403
00:33:46.443 --> 00:33:48.445
- Tough breakup?
- Yeah. you have no idea.

404
00:33:50.822 --> 00:33:53.242
Well. I don't know what he did to you…

405
00:33:54.159 --> 00:33:55.369
Make it two.

406
00:33:55.452 --> 00:33:57.329
But. in my experience.

407
00:33:58.163 --> 00:33:59.706
and this is what I have to offer.

408
00:34:00.290 --> 00:34:04.294
if he didn't treat you well. then it's
more about his damage than yours.

409
00:34:05.128 --> 00:34:06.463
You know?

410
00:34:08.090 --> 00:34:09.299
Yeah.

411
00:34:10.007 --> 00:34:12.803
That was… Thank you so much.

412
00:34:12.886 --> 00:34:15.764
I needed somebody
to say that to me today. Wow.

413
00:34:15.848 --> 00:34:19.226
Validation from strangers
is as objective as it gets.

414
00:34:19.726 --> 00:34:21.436
So don't take it lightly. honestly.

415
00:34:21.520 --> 00:34:23.105
And you know what else they say?

416
00:34:23.188 --> 00:34:24.648
- No. what do they say?
- Yes.

417
00:34:24.731 --> 00:34:28.150
They say that living well
is the best revenge…

418
00:34:32.489 --> 00:34:34.491
…and we're gonna say
good riddance to bad rubbish.

419
00:34:34.574 --> 00:34:36.659
- Fuck yeah. Great.
- Yeah.

420
00:34:39.204 --> 00:34:40.205
You good?

421
00:34:40.289 --> 00:34:42.206
- Yep. I…
- Okay.

422
00:34:43.333 --> 00:34:45.168
I need to go home. I need to go.

423
00:34:45.252 --> 00:34:47.814
Well. look. the ride shares here
can take like an hour to show up.

424
00:34:47.838 --> 00:34:49.005
But my office is. like…

425
00:34:49.755 --> 00:34:51.435
I have an office. like. across the street.

426
00:34:53.135 --> 00:34:54.928
I can take you there. I'll make you coffee.

427
00:34:55.596 --> 00:34:57.196
I can call you a car service from there.

428
00:34:57.472 --> 00:34:58.807
It's safe. it's warm.

429
00:35:04.313 --> 00:35:07.691
Thought about it. Okay. listen up. Focus.

430
00:35:09.526 --> 00:35:13.280
I may be drunk.
but you don't wanna mess with me.

431
00:35:13.363 --> 00:35:14.364
I can see that.

432
00:35:16.283 --> 00:35:17.743
That's a bad idea.

433
00:35:17.826 --> 00:35:18.952
This is us.

434
00:35:19.036 --> 00:35:20.037
Well…

435
00:35:21.538 --> 00:35:23.415
Nice view.

436
00:35:24.124 --> 00:35:25.125
Thank you.

437
00:35:26.293 --> 00:35:28.128
Well. what do you do. fancy-pants?

438
00:35:29.087 --> 00:35:30.714
Real estate.

439
00:35:30.797 --> 00:35:32.174
He does real estate.

440
00:35:32.257 --> 00:35:33.842
I do real estate.

441
00:35:33.926 --> 00:35:35.302
La-di-da.

442
00:35:35.385 --> 00:35:37.679
Can I get you a nightcap? You want scotch?

443
00:35:39.473 --> 00:35:40.974
I mean. what's one more drink?

444
00:35:41.558 --> 00:35:43.101
- Scotch.
- Well. I mean.

445
00:35:43.185 --> 00:35:46.688
it's just one more drink. I guess.

446
00:35:46.772 --> 00:35:48.398
- Exactly.
- Right.

447
00:35:49.858 --> 00:35:50.859
Drink.

448
00:35:51.818 --> 00:35:52.978
- Thank you.
- Now. come here.

449
00:35:53.487 --> 00:35:56.823
You're single. right?

450
00:35:57.324 --> 00:35:59.660
Yes. I am. How could you tell?

451
00:35:59.743 --> 00:36:00.786
Well. no ring.

452
00:36:02.371 --> 00:36:03.914
No pictures.

453
00:36:05.290 --> 00:36:08.794
I can read the room.
I'm very. very good at that.

454
00:36:08.877 --> 00:36:09.878
You are?

455
00:36:11.630 --> 00:36:13.048
You know what else you are?

456
00:36:13.924 --> 00:36:14.925
Shit-faced?

457
00:36:15.884 --> 00:36:17.427
No. I was gonna say beautiful.

458
00:36:19.972 --> 00:36:21.014
Well. that's nice.

459
00:36:27.646 --> 00:36:30.148
- You're so fucking hot.
- Okay.

460
00:36:31.275 --> 00:36:33.193
No. no. no. No. no. Wait. wait…

461
00:36:33.277 --> 00:36:34.736
No. no. no.

462
00:36:34.820 --> 00:36:36.864
Ew. I need to call…

463
00:36:37.406 --> 00:36:39.533
I need to call my roommate.

464
00:36:39.616 --> 00:36:42.452
- Jesus. Down. boy.
- Okay.

465
00:36:44.621 --> 00:36:46.039
Can I use your phone?

466
00:36:46.748 --> 00:36:48.959
- I'm pretty sure my one's dead.
- What?

467
00:36:50.294 --> 00:36:52.462
- Why?
- Yeah. 'cause my phone's dead.

468
00:36:52.546 --> 00:36:54.315
- Okay.
- We'll call my roommate. Do the thing.

469
00:36:54.339 --> 00:36:55.883
- you know.
- Okay. Yeah. of course.

470
00:36:55.966 --> 00:36:57.009
Thank you.

471
00:36:58.051 --> 00:37:01.305
Here. One second. Here.

472
00:37:01.388 --> 00:37:03.307
Thank you so much.

473
00:37:12.149 --> 00:37:13.901
I thought you said your phone was dead.

474
00:37:16.570 --> 00:37:18.447
You also thought I was drunk.

475
00:37:18.947 --> 00:37:20.824
Wrong. On both counts.

476
00:37:20.908 --> 00:37:24.203
I just texted myself your wife's
information. Beautiful. by the way.

477
00:37:24.286 --> 00:37:26.556
You know. just to tell her
that you were about to force yourself

478
00:37:26.580 --> 00:37:28.665
onto an inebriated woman in your office.

479
00:37:29.416 --> 00:37:32.377
Do you wanna FaceTime her together?
That could be cute.

480
00:37:32.461 --> 00:37:33.712
What the fuck is happening?

481
00:37:33.795 --> 00:37:36.107
- What are you talk...
- Well. it's called a shakedown. Eric.

482
00:37:36.131 --> 00:37:38.258
And trust me. you're gonna get off light.

483
00:37:38.759 --> 00:37:41.595
Just give me the access codes
and keys to one of your lease properties.

484
00:37:41.678 --> 00:37:44.056
and I will be out of your hair forever.

485
00:37:44.139 --> 00:37:45.432
The fuck is wrong with you?

486
00:37:45.516 --> 00:37:46.517
Plenty.

487
00:37:47.017 --> 00:37:51.271
But honestly. dude.
right now it's about your damage not mine.

488
00:37:54.691 --> 00:37:55.692
Hey.

489
00:37:55.776 --> 00:37:57.528
You don't sound like yourself.

490
00:37:57.611 --> 00:38:00.239
I'm tired and I'm in a mood.
I'm pretty sure I do.

491
00:38:01.156 --> 00:38:03.450
Well. you're gonna like
what I have to say.

492
00:38:04.243 --> 00:38:05.619
Try me.

493
00:38:07.037 --> 00:38:08.580
I see you. boy.

494
00:38:20.592 --> 00:38:23.971
I know the clock is ticking.
Spare me the threats.

495
00:38:24.805 --> 00:38:26.306
Your tone…

496
00:38:28.308 --> 00:38:31.895
Makes me wonder if you are feeling
the gravity of this situation.

497
00:38:33.105 --> 00:38:36.108
You were right.
Cary did buy a car. all cash.

498
00:38:36.191 --> 00:38:38.527
It says here
it was a blue Heritage Bronco.

499
00:38:38.610 --> 00:38:41.488
- You sure?
- I'm positive. One hundred percent.

500
00:38:42.155 --> 00:38:45.576
You lost ten million dollars.
Believe me. I get it.

501
00:38:45.659 --> 00:38:47.703
I didn't lose anything. You lost it.

502
00:38:47.786 --> 00:38:50.038
And you know
this isn't just about the money.

503
00:38:52.416 --> 00:38:54.626
It's about a zero-tolerance policy.

504
00:38:55.252 --> 00:38:56.503
No one steals from me.

505
00:38:57.171 --> 00:38:59.840
Wayne. this is my son.

506
00:39:01.383 --> 00:39:05.762
I know. Which is why I'm telling you
right now that it would be a mistake

507
00:39:05.846 --> 00:39:08.932
for you to worry about him.
when you should be worrying about me.

508
00:39:09.016 --> 00:39:10.976
because there is only one version of this

509
00:39:11.059 --> 00:39:13.478
that still has you breathing when it's over.

510
00:39:13.562 --> 00:39:15.063
Tell me you understand.

511
00:39:16.023 --> 00:39:17.357
I understand.

512
00:39:17.441 --> 00:39:19.443
You got a license plate I can run?

513
00:39:19.526 --> 00:39:22.905
No. I can do you one better.
I got his new ID.

514
00:39:24.406 --> 00:39:25.866
Meet me at the office.

515
00:39:26.450 --> 00:39:27.659
